vice quality for existing users while addressing underlying issues. Regulatory Risks Risk: Data Privacy Regulation Changes Evolving privacy regulations could impact our operations or create compliance burdens. Mitigation Strategy: Our zero-knowledge architecture inherently addresses many regulatory concerns by ensuring user data remains encrypted and inaccessible to Koda. We'll maintain relationships with privacy law experts to stay ahead of regulatory changes and design our systems for privacy by default. Contingency Plan: If significant regulatory changes occur, our modular architecture allows for region- specific adaptations while maintaining our core privacy principles. -- 17 of 22 -- 16 Risk: Encryption Regulation Some jurisdictions have proposed legislation that could impact strong encryption technologies. Mitigation Strategy: We'll actively monitor regulatory developments and participate in industry advocacy for strong encryption. Our legal team will develop jurisdiction-specific approaches that balance compliance with our fundamental privacy commitments. Contingency Plan: If necessary, we would implement jurisdiction-specific versions of the application while maintaining maximum possible privacy protections within legal constraints. Operational Risks Risk: Team Scaling Challenges Rapid growth could create organizational strain and cultural dilution. Mitigation Strategy: We've developed a structured onboarding process and clear documentation of our values and practices. Key hires will prioritize cultural fit alongside technical skills, and we'll implement regular team health assessments to identify issues early. Contingency Plan: If scaling challenges emerge, we would temporarily slow hiring to focus on team integration and cultural reinforcement before resuming growth. Risk: Dependency Risks Reliance on third-party services could create vulnerabilities if those services change or fail. Mitigation Strategy: We'll minimize critical dependencies and implement r