ble hyperparameter, but a value between 5 and 10 is often a good starting point. Returning too few chunks may miss important context, while returning too many can introduce noise and increase the cost of the generation step. Re-ranking (Optional but Recommended): A simple vector similarity search is powerful, but it can sometimes be improved with a re-ranking step. A re-ranker model can take the top k retrieved chunks and re-order them based on a more sophisticated understanding of relevance. For example, a cross-encoder model can look at the query and a document chunk simultaneously to produce a more accurate relevance score. This adds a small amount of latency but can significantly improve the quality of the retrieved context. Context Assembly: The top k (and potentially re-ranked) document chunks are then assembled into a single block of text. This text, which we will call the "context, " is the information that will be provided to the Large Language Model in the next stage. It is crucial to format this context clearly, often with metadata indicating the source of each chunk, to help the LLM understand the information it is being given. World-Class Prompts for Retrieval (Internal System Logic): ‚Ä¢ **Prompt for Query Processing: ** Advanced Formal AI Prompt System Role You are a Senior Python Developer specializing in architecting and implementing core components of AI-driven data pipelines. Your responsibility is to deliver clean, efficient, and production-ready Python code that is well-documented and includes robust error handling. Objective Your objective is to generate the complete technical specification and production-ready Python code for a critical function: embed_user_query. This function is a core component of a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system, responsible for converting a user's natural language question into a vector embedding. Established Architecture & Technology Stack Language: Python Architecture: The function will be a part of a large