tion and Recovery Koda anticipates common errors and prevents them proactively. For example, the interface warns users before uploading unsupported file types. When errors do occur, clear messages explain what went wrong and how to fix it. This reduces frustration and builds user confidence. Principle 6: Consistency Visual elements, interaction patterns, and terminology remain consistent throughout the interface. Users learn once and apply everywhere. This consistency extends to response formatting, citation styles, and error messages, creating a predictable and reliable experience. Principle 7: User Control Users maintain control over the conversation at all times. They can stop generation mid-response, regenerate answers, edit their messages, and delete conversations. This sense of control reduces anxiety and encourages experimentation. Principle 8: Accessibility Koda is designed to be accessible to users with disabilities. The interface supports screen readers, keyboard navigation, and high-contrast modes. Text is readable, buttons are large enough to click, and color is never the only means of conveying information. Principle 9: Mobile Optimization The interface adapts seamlessly to mobile devices, recognizing that many users access Koda from smartphones. Touch targets are appropriately sized, text is readable without zooming, and the layout adjusts to different screen sizes. Principle 10: Trust and Transparency Koda builds trust through transparency about its capabilities and limitations. It acknowledges when it doesn‚Äôt know something, cites sources when possible, and warns users about potential inaccuracies. This honesty creates realistic expectations and prevents disappointment. Principle 11: Continuous Improvement The interface evolves based on user feedback and usage patterns. Koda continuously refines the experience, adding features that users request and removing friction points. This commitment to improvement keeps Koda at the forefront of AI assistant