r freemium model (Free, Personal, Premium, Family tiers) ensures broad market access while driving conversion to high-margin (80-92%) paid plans, fueled by the tangible value of our AI features. Koda's defensible moat lies in its unique fusion of conversational AI, a rigorously implemented zero knowledge security architecture (detailed in the Technical Architecture section), and proactive document intelligence. Existing players like Dropbox, Google Drive, Evernote, or LastPass excel in narrow domains but fail to deliver the holistic, secure, and intuitive experience Koda provides. Our competitive analysis highlights Koda's distinct advantages in semantic understanding, true user privacy, and proactive assistance. We are seeking $500, 000 in pre-seed funding to complete product development, launch go-to-market initiatives, and drive early user acquisition. This capital will support our path to reaching 100, 000 total users and 7, 000 paying subscribers in Year 1, with breakeven projected by Year 2 and revenue scaling to over $6. 2 million by Year 3. For investors, Koda represents a compelling opportunity to back a defensible, high-retention SaaS platform addressing a widespread need in personal and professional document management‚Äîsupported by proprietary AI, zero-knowledge architecture, and a freemium model with strong conversion economics. Projected investor outcomes range from 6. 0x to 18. 0x MOIC and ~50% to 75% IRR, based on conservative to optimistic strategic exit scenarios. Koda is not just managing documents; we are bringing peace of mind, security, and intelligence to the core of our users' digital lives. We invite you to join us in ending digital chaos. MISSION & VISION Mission: Koda‚Äôs mission is to bring clarity, control, and intelligence to the way individuals manage their most vital personal information. We transform fragmented, passive document storage into a secure, AI-powered assistant that actively supports users‚Äô lives‚Äîanticipating needs, simplifying complexity, and restoring peace of mind. Vision: We envision a world where personal information management is invisible yet indispensable‚Äîwhere every individual has a trusted digital partner that safeguards their most critical documents, answers important life questions, and acts before chaos can occur. Koda aims to become the gold standard for intelligent, privacy-first document management across the globe. MARKET PROBLEM: FRAGMENTED DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT Consumer Pain Analysis: Systemic Inefficiencies The promise of the digital age‚Äîinstant access to information‚Äîhas ironically created a new form of chaos for personal documents. Consider the lived experiences behind the statistics: Sarah, the Overwhelmed Professional: After a fender bender, panic sets in. Was the insurance policy saved in Dropbox? Google Drive? An email attachment from six months ago? Hours are wasted searching, stress levels skyrocket, and a simple administrative task becomes a crisis. Multiply this by hundreds of critical documents‚Äîcontracts, tax forms, property deeds‚Äîand the cumulative time lost, and anxiety generated becomes staggering. For professionals like Sarah (35% of our target market), this isn't just inconvenient; it's a drain on productivity and mental well-being, costing them an average of 4. 2 hours per month. Michael, the Juggling Freelancer: For Michael, time is literally money. Every minute spent hunting for a client contract, verifying invoice details, or organizing tax receipts is a minute not spent on billable work. The lack of a centralized, intelligent system leads to missed deadlines, delayed payments, and strained client relationships. The constant low-level stress of potential disorganization impacts not just his bottom line, but his ability to grow his business. Elena, the Dutiful Caregiver: Managing her elderly father's affairs involves navigating a labyrinth of medical records, insurance policies, legal directives, and financial statements. A misplaced