te a perfect storm: an explosion in digital documents coupled with heightened user expectations for security, intelligence, and accessibility. Koda is engineered precisely for this moment. Target Market Segmentation: Strategic Focus While the pain is universal, specific segments feel it most acutely: Busy Professionals (35%): Time-poor, security-conscious, juggling ~267 documents/year. Pain Points: Wasted search time (4. 2 hrs/month), multi-device security anxiety. Koda Value: Instant retrieval via conversation, zero-knowledge security peace of mind. Parents (19%): Managing family documents (~317/year). Pain Points: Version control chaos (73% confused), secure sharing complexity. Koda Value: Centralized family hub, granular secure sharing, automatic organization. Freelancers/SMB Owners (13%): Managing business-critical documents. Pain Points: Lost billable hours (5. 7 hrs/month), deadline anxiety. Koda Value: Streamlined organization, quick access to contracts/invoices, reduced administrative overhead. Doctors / Healthcare Professionals (21%): Balancing demanding clinical responsibilities with personal administration. Pain Points: Managing licenses, CME credits, certifications, personal insurance, and financial documents amidst intense time pressure; risk of mixing personal files with patient data on work systems; need for rapid, secure access to credentials. Koda Value: Dedicated, secure vault for personal life admin separate from clinical systems; instant AI powered retrieval of licenses/certificates; proactive reminders for renewals/CMEs; zero knowledge security for sensitive personal data. Elderly & Caregivers (5%): High-stakes document management (medical, legal, financial). Pain Points: Overwhelm, severe consequences of mismanagement (67% report issues). Koda Value: Simplified access, proactive reminders, secure sharing with trusted parties. Students (7%): Navigating adult documentation for the first time. Pain Points: Lack of system, feeling overwhelmed (78%)