 of digital information management. Technical Architecture: Security and Intelligence Framework Koda's competitive advantage is rooted in its sophisticated, purpose-built technology: Zero-Knowledge Architecture Explained: Client-Side Encryption: Every file is encrypted with AES-256 on the user's device using a unique key derived from their password via PBKDF2 (with a high iteration count to thwart brute-force attacks) before a single byte is transmitted. No Server-Side Decryption: Koda servers store only encrypted blobs of data. We never receive or store user passwords or decryption keys. This means we cannot decrypt user data, even if compelled by legal order or in the event of a server breach. Secure Key Management: User access relies on strong credentials combined with biometric options and a user-controlled BIP39 recovery phrase for account recovery, maintaining the zero-knowledge principle throughout the lifecycle. End-to-End Encrypted Sharing: Sharing utilizes asymmetric cryptography to ensure only the intended recipient can decrypt shared files, with granular, revocable permissions. Semantic AI Engine ‚Äì The 'Brain': Multi-Stage NLP Pipeline: Documents undergo OCR (if needed), layout analysis, entity recognition (NER for dates, names, organizations, monetary values, etc. ), relationship extraction, and semantic indexing. Custom Language Models: While leveraging foundational models, we fine-tune specialized models trained on diverse document types (contracts, invoices, IDs, medical records) for superior accuracy in understanding domain-specific language and structures. Vector Embeddings & Semantic Search: Documents and queries are converted into vector representations, allowing searches based on meaning and context, not just keywords. This enables finding conceptually related information even if the exact terms aren't used. Cross-Document Synthesis: Our AI builds a knowledge graph from the user's documents (within their encrypted environment), enabling it to 